    "Alternatively, using open-source LLMs, for example through the 'Ollama' package [26,27], would allow tighter LLM version control and allow better reproducibility of responses.",
    "Many open-source LLMs can be downloaded and used locally [26], which would enable the same LLM model version to be used.We believe that the prompts developed within this study are generalisable to NMAs in different disease areas, and similar prompts can be used for continuous outcomes; however, there is a need to demonstrate that this is the case.",
